Dialogue: 0,0:00:04.20,0:00:05.86,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}There's something fascinating about stars,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:05.86,0:00:07.67,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}be they criminals or actors.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:07.67,0:00:10.97,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}The Detective Boys work together\Nto explain the teleportation trick!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:10.97,0:00:12.85,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}The brooch is the key to the confession!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:12.85,0:00:14.46,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}He sees the single truth for what it is,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:14.46,0:00:16.18,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}and looks like a kid but has the mind of an adult.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:16.18,0:00:18.18,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}His name? Detective Conan!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.00,0:03:29.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,(Title Card)
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.84,0:03:35.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,All else aside,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.25,0:03:39.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,it's incontrovertible fact that Takagi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} witnessed a jewelry store robbery
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.34,0:03:42.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and managed to corner the robber on top of a building,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.18,0:03:48.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,but allowed the suspect to commit suicide before his very eyes!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.18,0:03:49.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.56,0:03:53.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It seems fishy that he happened to fall onto a moving truck
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.73,0:03:59.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,that was relocating furniture from the office he was just fired from.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.15,0:04:02.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But there's no reason to believe it wasn't a suicide.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.08,0:04:09.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then let's call it a day for now.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.54,0:04:14.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Nekota{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, can you drop by the police station tonight?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.04,0:04:16.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What? W-Why is that?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.30,0:04:21.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,As his former employer, maybe you can answer some questions
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.05,0:04:24.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,about his personality and what might have driven him to this.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.89,0:04:26.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, right.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.89,0:04:26.35,Character Card,,0,0,0,,Sakanobu Nekota (51)\NOwner of an import-export company
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.31,0:04:28.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No problem.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.93,0:04:32.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A little lower... Lower!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.48,0:04:34.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Just a little more!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.94,0:04:40.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What are you kids up to?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.15,0:04:42.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,N-Nothing!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.61,0:04:46.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, ma'am! We have questions!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.45,0:04:47.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Questions?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.37,0:04:48.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.49,0:04:50.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Two questions for Nekota{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.67,0:04:55.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Me?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.35,0:05:12.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,As we recall, when you arrived at the scene of the crime,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.56,0:05:18.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,you told Detective Takagi to "hurry up and do whatever you cops have to do."
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.57,0:05:20.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, so?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.99,0:05:23.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What made you say that?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.36,0:05:26.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, of course I was very busy andâ€”
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.16,0:05:27.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's not what we're asking you!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.67,0:05:40.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So how did you know he was a police detective?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.89,0:05:54.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,W-Well, a criminal had fallen to his death! Of course I assumed the police were there.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.81,0:05:59.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But you also asked what was goin' on!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.07,0:06:04.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And you told us you'd never met the detectives before!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.95,0:06:06.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You're right!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.99,0:06:10.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If he didn't know anything about the case and had never seen us before,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.91,0:06:13.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,it doesn't make sense that he knew Takagi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} was a cop!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.62,0:06:17.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I-It was just the atmosphere of the crime scene!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.04,0:06:22.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I-I could tell that something terrible had happened and figured the police would be there...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.92,0:06:25.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And now for the second question!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.05,0:06:29.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We've been in your apartment for a while now.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.76,0:06:33.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So why haven't you yelled at us?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.44,0:06:41.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We're kids!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.07,0:06:44.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If we were grown-ups, you might assume we're with the police.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.28,0:06:49.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But if a group of strange kids ran into your house, surely you'd say...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.28,0:06:52.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"What are those brats doing here?"
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.58,0:06:55.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,T-That...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.08,0:06:59.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Since you haven't questioned our presence, you must know we belong here.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.67,0:07:05.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You know we're key witnesses to the jewelry store robbery.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.01,0:07:13.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Do you?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.14,0:07:14.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, er...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.22,0:07:14.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Waitasec...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.93,0:07:17.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If he knew I was an officer,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.14,0:07:20.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and also knew the kids were involved...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.52,0:07:24.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,t-then...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.73,0:07:27.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You must have been...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.07,0:07:29.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The robber!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.28,0:07:35.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Right. That would answer both of Mitsuhiko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}'s questions.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.79,0:07:37.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,D-Don't be absurd!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.20,0:07:39.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Think about it!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.33,0:07:45.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The robber jumped off the building across the street and fell onto the truck, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.63,0:07:52.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If I was the robber, where did I disappear after I jumped?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.14,0:07:56.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And how do you explain Atomura{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s body on the truck?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.02,0:08:01.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Anyway, I'm 51 years old!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.15,0:08:05.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I don't have the strength to lead the police on a chase.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.99,0:08:10.11,Radio,,0,0,0,,{\be10}The triathlons.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.66,0:08:16.58,Radio,,0,0,0,,{\be10}For someone who trains for such a grueling sport,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.58,0:08:18.12,Radio,,0,0,0,,{\be10}it wouldn't be much of a problem!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.46,0:08:23.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}'s voice!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.00,0:08:25.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I was wondering where that kid had gone.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.92,0:08:28.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Where are you, Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.84,0:08:30.05,Radio,,0,0,0,,{\be10}I'm climbing the fire escape...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.80,0:08:32.55,Radio,,0,0,0,,{\be10}to the roof of the building the robber jumped from!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.80,0:08:36.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I wanted to test something,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.14,0:08:40.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,so I asked the others to buy me time with their questions.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.56,0:08:42.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,W-What are you testing?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.28,0:08:55.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Can you see me from there?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.96,0:09:02.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I-I can, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.75,0:09:04.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What are you planning to do?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.96,0:09:11.09,Radio,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Remember that lady who lives over Mr. Nekota's place?{split style, line needs rewrite}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.09,0:09:14.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She woke up around 2 AM to a heavy thudding sound.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.89,0:09:17.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When she looked over at the window,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.47,0:09:21.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,she saw a thin, stick-like shadow against the curtain.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.85,0:09:27.23,Radio,,0,0,0,,{\be10}I thought you should know I've solved the mystery behind that!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.23,0:09:28.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,C-Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.82,0:09:30.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Cut this out at once!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.40,0:09:32.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm cooperating with the police out of the goodness of my heart
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.95,0:09:35.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,because a former employee of mine was involved!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.16,0:09:38.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Now it looks like these children want to pin the crime on me!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.78,0:09:43.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But who'd believe a silly children's story?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.79,0:09:46.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Again, like I said,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.92,0:09:48.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,if I was the robber,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.21,0:09:51.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,how did I disappear from the top of that building?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.01,0:09:54.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's impossible! It couldn't happen!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.17,0:09:59.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Not unless I had the power to teleport from the roof...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.43,0:10:01.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It is possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.07,0:10:16.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You don't need magic powers.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.53,0:10:18.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You see?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.99,0:10:20.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,C-Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}?!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.08,0:10:23.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How'd you get here?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.87,0:10:27.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,With this rope I borrowed from the movers!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.50,0:10:30.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Rope?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.55,0:10:35.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,First, I measured the length from the balcony of the old office
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.22,0:10:38.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,to the balcony of this room, four stories below.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.89,0:10:41.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then I found a rope that was about twice that length,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.31,0:10:44.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,wrapped it around the railing of the upper balcony
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.22,0:10:46.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and tied the ends together to make a big loop!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.77,0:10:51.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I added a smaller loop, just big enough to fit me,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.82,0:10:56.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and threw it to the rooftop to the building across the street,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.90,0:10:58.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,just like the robber did.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.66,0:11:05.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The robber climbed onto the rooftop and pretended to be cornered.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.37,0:11:10.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He tied the rope around himself, hiding it under his heavy coat.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.38,0:11:20.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When he jumped, the rope swung him down to this balcony.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.10,0:11:24.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Once he made it across the street,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.85,0:11:26.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,he just needed to untie the rope and hide it in his room!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.10,0:11:32.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.06,0:11:37.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{line needs rewrite}Conan, you could've been hurt! Slamming into a wall like that...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.15,0:11:40.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I wore a helmet, just like the robber.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.74,0:11:45.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And I got this big soccer ball from Doc's ball-shooting belt...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.12,0:11:48.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and used it as a cushion! I'm fine!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.38,0:11:59.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I think Nekota{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} used a mattress as a cushion instead.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.99,0:12:23.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mattress?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.70,0:12:26.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I checked it a while ago, and it's wet!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.46,0:12:35.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was out in the rain, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.42,0:12:39.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then the strange noises and shadows Isaka{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} noticed
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.59,0:12:42.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,were Nekota{line needs tweaking} practicing his moves...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.93,0:12:47.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,W-Wait! When you looked down after the robber jumped,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.47,0:12:50.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,you saw a body on the truck!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.27,0:12:52.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Where did that come from?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.90,0:12:55.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was on the truck from the start!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.23,0:13:02.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{line needs rewrite}Mr. Atomura fell onto the truck and was killed
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.11,0:13:04.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,after the movers parked outside of the back door of the building this morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.78,0:13:10.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{line needs rewrite}You called Mr. Atomura over, saying you needed help with the moving or something,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.59,0:13:28.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,then shoved him out the window and onto the truck.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.39,0:13:36.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{line needs rewrite}Come to think of it, Nekota said his company used to take up the whole ninth floor...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.98,0:13:40.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{line needs rewrite}He could've easily lured Atomura to a window and pushed him!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.82,0:13:41.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But the noise!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.40,0:13:47.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Someone would've heard a body falling!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.03,0:13:52.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Not with that construction work in the alley.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.25,0:14:01.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It'd be entirely possible to shove someone out a window without attracting notice.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.05,0:14:07.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,B-But the truck would shake when the body fell! The driver would notice!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.14,0:14:14.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's why you made everybody, including the driver, come up for a meeting in the office!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.23,0:14:18.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The movers told me you kept them waiting for a long time.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.15,0:14:22.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's when you shoved Atomura{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} out the window,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.28,0:14:26.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,created the rope gimmick and shut the blinds!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.78,0:14:31.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Even if the movers went into the office, they wouldn't see anything wrong.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.41,0:14:35.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see. It was like this...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.08,0:14:39.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{line needs rewrite}First Nekota had all the movers come up to the top floor,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.59,0:14:42.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,where his company used to be located.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.05,0:14:47.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He made them wait while he killed Atomura{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} by shoving him out the window,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.89,0:14:52.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,then threw the rope over to the rooftop of the building across the street.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.35,0:14:55.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,While the movers were moving boxes into the new office,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.39,0:14:58.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,he put on his disguise, raided the jewelry store,{out of synch}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.85,0:15:02.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,ran to the roof of the other building with Takagi on his tail,{line needs rewrite}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.15,0:15:04.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and used the rope to swing across the street into his apartment.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.78,0:15:07.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It looked like a criminal cornered by the police
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.65,0:15:12.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,had committed suicide by jumping from the building!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.99,0:15:13.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Right!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.83,0:15:16.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And if he dropped the bag with the jewels,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.41,0:15:21.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,or the extra helmet he'd placed on the rooftop beforehand,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.05,0:15:28.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,he could still use the noise to make people think something had fallen on the truck!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.13,0:15:33.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's why the body wasn't wearing a helmet!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.68,0:15:38.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then the reason the robber grinned when he found out I was a police officer...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.27,0:15:50.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,was because he needed someone to chase him and watch him jump off the building!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.16,0:15:57.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If you hadn't been there, he probably would've stalled for time until the police showed up.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.37,0:16:01.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But this plan relies too much on luck.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.67,0:16:07.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If anyone had found the body too early, or seen the rope setup,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.55,0:16:09.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,it would've fallen apart.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.38,0:16:15.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's such a sloppy plan, a child saw through it!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.10,0:16:17.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It wasn't because of luck that nobody noticed those things.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.68,0:16:18.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.93,0:16:20.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was the weather.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.02,0:16:25.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Rain...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.15,0:16:26.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I get it!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.27,0:16:29.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Nobody was out on their balconies or looking up at the sky!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.82,0:16:33.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Everybody on the street had umbrellas over their heads...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.91,0:16:37.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And nobody would see the body unless they went out on a balcony and looked down!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.66,0:16:41.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And the truck drove along a little-used back alley.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.62,0:16:44.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,To get caught, he'd have to be very unlucky.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.59,0:16:50.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.43,0:16:58.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Come on! He couldn't have predicted the weather! It was a lucky break!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.18,0:17:00.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No it wasn't!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.02,0:17:02.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You changed the moving day twice, didn't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.81,0:17:04.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You were waiting for rain!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.82,0:17:08.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,All we need now is proof...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.48,0:17:13.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,W-We ought to find plenty of evidence in this building.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.95,0:17:18.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Nekota{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} appeared downstairs not long after the robber jumped.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.74,0:17:27.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So the rope, helmet, raincoat, and the brooch I was going to buy...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.67,0:17:35.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,should all still be around here.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.05,0:17:42.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's right. He didn't have time to destroy the evidence or throw it far away,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.06,0:17:48.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,so it should still be in or around the building.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.57,0:17:51.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If the brooch is still in the coat,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.49,0:17:55.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and we find your fingerprints and hair on the helmet,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.20,0:18:03.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,you'll give up, won't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.84,0:18:21.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But why'd you pocket that brooch?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.35,0:18:25.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was a token of apology, I guess.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.52,0:18:27.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.52,0:18:33.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,My company was going under, and the only way to rebuild it
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.15,0:18:38.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,was to fire all the employees who were close to retirement.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.29,0:18:44.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He was one of them.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.37,0:18:53.55,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}If you fire me, I'll go public about our long history of deliberate food mislabeling!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.46,0:18:55.42,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}What?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.42,0:18:58.76,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Let me stay on until retirement.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.76,0:19:03.64,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}I just want to be able to buy this brooch for my wife's birthday.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.64,0:19:09.98,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}You know, she may want even more expensive jewelry later on.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.98,0:19:12.52,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}But let's not worry about that for now.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.78,0:19:15.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's why you did it?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.24,0:19:17.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.36,0:19:21.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I was afraid that if I agreed, he'd continue to blackmail me.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.66,0:19:24.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But why take the brooch?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.58,0:19:29.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I was going to give it to his wife on her birthday,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.08,0:19:33.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and claim he'd entrusted me with it before his death.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.13,0:19:39.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He'd worked hard for this company since the day we started.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.76,0:19:48.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And here I was, his murderer, about to frame him for a crime he didn't commit.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.77,0:19:53.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When I saw that brooch, I grabbed it out of guilt.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.70,0:20:10.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Guess it ended up convicting me.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:42.92,0:21:47.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Where's the brooch? Where's the coat?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:47.01,0:21:49.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In my bedroom closet.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:49.60,0:21:50.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You heard him!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:50.27,0:21:52.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Check it out, Sato{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:52.35,0:21:53.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Uh... sure...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:59.52,0:22:00.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Here it is!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:02.07,0:22:03.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It must be the damp one!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:05.45,0:22:07.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm sure you'll like it!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:09.74,0:22:13.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Detective Takagi spent a long time picking it out!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:13.33,0:22:15.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It doesn't have any big gems!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:15.54,0:22:19.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's a decent choice. The man must know your tastes.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:19.00,0:22:20.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why don't you look at it?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:30.14,0:22:32.85,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}{possibly this needs tuning}That's right, Miwako.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:32.85,0:22:36.60,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}I caught Miwako staring at this brooch like it was Japan's most wanted!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:36.60,0:22:39.36,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}If you want to wow her, this is the one to buy!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:39.36,0:22:42.44,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}But remember, don't tell her I told you.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:42.44,0:22:46.99,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}If she thinks it's a coincidence, it'll deepen your love!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:47.99,0:22:50.20,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Let's deepen...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:50.20,0:22:52.41,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}our l-l-love...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:52.91,0:22:53.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:54.87,0:22:57.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This
Dialogue: 0,0:22:58.38,0:22:59.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,brooch...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:01.34,0:23:03.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Isn't this the brooch Yumi wanted?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:07.55,0:23:08.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Y-Yumi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:08.59,0:23:11.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah. She saw it in some magazine!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:12.22,0:23:19.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Say, I saw Yumi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} wearing a bracelet that looked a lot like the one I gave you once...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:19.56,0:23:21.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, I loaned it to her!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:23.15,0:23:25.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She said it was just her style!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:28.57,0:23:32.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I've never had much interest in sparkly stuff.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:34.54,0:23:37.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ooh, what a gorgeous necklace!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:39.67,0:23:44.09,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}I'll get Lt. Takano to buy this one...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:46.13,0:23:49.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, Conan! Come here, come here!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:49.63,0:23:52.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Someone asked us Detective Boys for help!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:52.85,0:23:54.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And this time it's...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:56.06,0:23:57.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yay!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:04.90,0:24:05.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Look out!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:08.70,0:24:09.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Everyone, hurry!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:10.82,0:24:15.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Next Conan: "The Mysterious Angel's Mansion (Part 1)"!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:17.00,0:24:21.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Next Conan's Hint: Charging{?} Bull
Dialogue: 0,0:24:21.62,0:24:23.21,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Next time, it's the beefiest present!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:23.21,0:24:24.42,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Huh? A cow?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:24.42,0:24:25.46,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Is that a no-go?
